HEADWORD: Dandruff
<hw>Dandruff</hw> <pr>(d⟦acr⟧n"dr⟦ucr⟧f)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Prob.
from W. <ets>ton</ets>crust, peel, skin + AS. <ets>dr⟦omac⟧f</ets>
dirty, draffy, or W. <ets>drwg</ets> bad: cf. AS. <ets>tan</ets> a
letter, an eruption. ⟦root⟧240.]</ety> <def>A scurf which forms on the
head, and comes off in small scales or particles.</def> <altsp>[Written
also <asp>dandriff</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

